      content:
        '<p><strong><a href="../person/36583">Rev John Harty</a></strong> entered St Patrick’s College, Maynooth in August 1867 and was ordained on 21 June 1874. Afterwards, Harty was appointed to St Patrick’s Church, Providence, Rhode Island. At the Sacred Heart Church in East Providence, Harty greatly reduced the church debt; built the handsome St Margaret’s Church in Rumford and in early 1897 he was appointed to the Church of the Sacred Heart in Pawtucket. Harty also held the office of State chaplain to the Knights of Columbanus.</p>',
